We also give comments on the gauge coupling unification.
Within the framework of minimal supersymmetric standard model (MSSM), 
three gauge couplings of  
meet around  GeV.
Suppose that the three gauge groups are originated from 
different sets of -branes.
If one can stabilize , 
the gauge couplings are universal at the string scale .
That implies .
Otherwise, if  is sizable, 
the gauge couplings are, in general, non-universal at .
However, one of interesting possibilities to explain 
the experimental values of gauge couplings is the 
so-called "mirage unification".
